<h2 id="change-the-chart-title">Change the Chart Title</h2>
<p>In the chart properties pane, under general, you can change the title of the chart so it is more concise and fits on the layout better.</p>

<p><img src="content/images/ChartTitle.png" alt="hi" class="inline" /></p>

<h2 id="resize-items-and-set-map-scale">Resize Items and Set Map Scale</h2>
<p>Resize the map and chart so the map is a bit bigger than the chart.  Then set the map scale to 1:100,000 and add the scale to the map.</p>

<h2 id="add-other-map-elements">Add Other Map Elements</h2>
<p>Add all the appropriate map elements: Title, Legend, North Arrow, and Source Statement.  You can reference previous Modules for a refresher on how to do this.</p>
<ul>
  <li>For the Data Source in you Name/Source Statement, list Stats Canada and Google Earth Engine as the data sources</li>
  <li>Your final map should look something like shown below.
    <ul>
      <li>The chart should show the relationship between green vegetation area and income.  The map should show mean NDVI value by DA.</li>
      <li>This map is just a rough guide, feel free to make your own stylistic choices to improve on it.  Your values should look a bit different, so don‚Äôt be concerned if the numbers don‚Äôt match perfectly!</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

